<h3>Schools Closed</h3>
<p>Dear Pepin Area Schools families: </p>
<p>The health and safety of our students and staff are always our number one priority. We have closed our school buildings under order to help contain the spread of COVID-19, the coronavirus in Wisconsin.</p>
<p>We know that keeping children at home may cause difficulties for your children and families as you juggle work, child care and other challenges, and our staff are committed to doing everything we can to help make this as positive an experience as possible for your children.</p>
<p>Gov. Tony Evers on March 23 issued a statewide <a data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://content.govdelivery.com/attachments/WIGOV/2020/03/24/file_attachments/1409408/Health%2520Order%2520%252312%2520Safer%2520At%2520Home.pdf&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585178619440000&amp;usg=AFQjCNETqZ2NHN3buY3yLSfkODMD0IhZNw" href="https://content.govdelivery.com/attachments/WIGOV/2020/03/24/file_attachments/1409408/Health%20Order%20%2312%20Safer%20At%20Home.pdf" target="_blank">"Safer-at-Home" order</a> requiring that from <strong>March 25-<span style="color:#ff0000;">May 26 (extended)</span></strong><span style="color:#ff0000;"> </span>residents stay at home except for certain activities such as getting groceries, gas, medicine and pet and medical supplies; engaging in outdoor activities like walking, running, biking and hiking if following six-foot social distancing guidelines; caring for others and working in essential businesses. Evers on March 13 had ordered the closure of all K-12 Wisconsin schools, public and private from Wednesday, March 18 to at least April 5 but later extended that to an "indefinite" period during the public health emergency.</p>
<p>“Kids and families across Wisconsin often depend on our schools to access food and care," Evers said. "We are going to continue working to do everything we can to ensure kids and families have the resources and support they need while schools are closed.”</p>
<p><strong><span style="color:#ff0000;">Pepin Area Schools will be closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year</span></strong>. All after-school activities and athletics, including practices, also will be canceled. </p>
<h4>School Meals</h4>
<p>The district will be delivering meals to all students who have signed up Monday-Friday.  For more information on meal deliveries, contact Bruce Quinton at 715-442-2391 or bruceq@pepin.k12.wi.us. </p>
<h4>Home WiFi options</h4>
<p>Some internet carriers are offering free and/or low cost options that your family may be able to use.</p>
<p>See <a href="https://dpi.wi.gov/broadband/home-internet-access" target="_blank">DPI list of internet offers for families</a></p>
